OL,3,CAlopecia patient: 'I didn't even look
OL,4,Cat myself in the mirror'
OL,6,F"I felt ashamed, guilty and I didn't
OL,7,Feven look at myself in the mirror. I
OL,8,Fjust survived, day by day, got by and
OL,9,Fcried a lot of tears."
OL,11,FElena did not tell anyone for five
OL,12,Fyears until she decided to embrace her
OL,13,Fhair loss when she became a mother and
OL,14,Fdid not want it to hold her back.
OL,16,FAlopecia is an autoimmune disease that
OL,17,Faffects one in 1000 people and occurs
OL,18,Fwhen the body attacks hair follicles
OL,19,Fwhich can cause hair loss.
